      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d be more explicit here about what is meant by \"the mapping\", since DHTNet actually creates multiple mappings when Jami starts:\n- One mapping is explicitly requested by the daemon with a specific port number for the DHT (in `JamiAccount::doRegister_`, relevant logs are `\"[Account {:s}] UPnP: requesting mapping for DHT port {}\"` and `\"[Account {:s}] DHT UPnP mapping changed to {:s}\"`).\n- The other mappings (12 by default: 4 TCP + 8 UDP) are created without having been explicitly requested (with random port numbers) as an optimization, to avoid later ICE negotiations being slowed down due to waiting for the router.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 134,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 134,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "dd8600559a1cf8da1f84b696aea536d136f136b7",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
